*
*    THE "DATA ARCHIVAL/RECOVERY SYSTEM" ("DARS") IS AN ISPF/PDF BASED
*    DIALOG THAT PROVIDES AUTOMATED DASD MANAGEMENT. IT REQUIRES DF/DSS
*    VERSION V2.3, TSO/E V1.3, AND ISPF/PDF V2.2. ESSENTIALLY, DARS IS
*    A MENU-DRIVEN UTILITY THAT AUTOMATES THE ARCHIVING AND RECOVERY
*    OF DASD DATA.  IT IS EASILY MODIFIABLE TO ACCOMODATE SPECIFIC
*    SITE NEEDS.  IN IT'S PRESENT FORM, AN OPERATOR, ON A QUARTERLY
*    SCHEDULE, MENU SELECTS A (DF/DSS) DUMP JOB SUBMITTAL THAT ARCHIVES
*    ALL PUBLIC STORAGE DATASETS THAT HAVE BEEN UNREFERENCED IN THE PAST
*    YEAR OR GREATER.  AN ONLINE RECORD OF ALL ARCHIVED DATA IS KEPT SO
*    THAT A USER MAY INQUIRE OF THE STATUS OF ARCHIVED DATASETS AS WELL
*    AS SUBMIT REQUESTS TO RECOVER ARCHIVED DATA.  PARTICULAR EFFORT WAS
*    PUT FORTH IN WRITING THIS UTILITY SO AS TO ENSURE DATA REDUNDANCY
*    FOR OBVIOUS CONTINGENCY PURPOSES.
*
